edm:ProvidedCHO.dc:title: Elliott Avent, coach
edm:ProvidedCHO.dc:description: Elliott Avent was already the third winningest coach in school history before entering this, his tenth, season. He has averaged more than 37 wins a year. Named ACC and National Coach of the Year in 2003, when he led the Wolfpack to its first NCAA super regional ever, Avent has taken the Wolfpack to six NCAA regionals. He is the first NC State baseball coach ever to be named National Coach of the Year, and only the third Wolfpack coach in any sport to be so honored.
